this earth, and which is two thirds of this earth. So, therefore, that mortal 
man who hath more of joy than sorrow in him, that mortal man cannot be 
true—not true, or undeveloped. With books the same. The truest of all men was 
the Man of Sorrows, and the truest of all books is Solomon’s, and 
Ecclesiastes is the fine hammered steel of woe. “All is vanity.” ALL. This 
